{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf28 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_synopsis_1}{\*\bkmkend co_synopsis_1}
{\b1 \cf28 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb400 
Synopsis
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Action brought by property owners for a determination of the legality of actions taken by the port authority in selling certain property and granting permission to fill in the bay in front of this property. The Circuit Court, Hillsborough County, C. Richard Leavengood, J., granted the port authority\rquote s motion to dismiss the complaint for declaratory judgment and the property owners appealed. The District Court of Appeal, Allen, J., held that complaint could not be maintained because all appellate review of rulings of port authority was required to be by certiorari.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf37 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
